<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-50-0103 </DOCNO><TEXT>The second part is devoted to the presentation of the accident surgeryaspects of knee lesions. For every topographical region the anatomicalfeatures, the most frequent causes of fractures, as well as the conventionalclassification criteria, are described. In each case also the principalsurgical methods are described. Lesions of tendons or ligaments havebeen included only insofar as they have occurred within the context ofan osseous lesion.</TEXT></DOC>